Bloody street brawl in Ilorin, Kwara State capital has led to death of two persons. The street disturbance allegedly occurred around Adifa and Centre Igboro areas of the metropolis on Friday. The victims, identifier as Lukman and Kudus, were stabbed to death by their attackers. Spokesperson of Kwara Police Ajayi Okasanmi confirmed the incident. Okasanmi said: “The attack was carried out by a group of boys led by one Habeeb Ganiyu of Agbarere area Ilorin, who stabbed the deceased several times in the chest.   BREAKING: Scores of free food seekers die in church stampede     UPDATED: Why I quit PDP presidential race, by Hayatu-Deen     BREAKING: Hayatu-Deen quits PDP presidential primary, says…   Read Also: Actress Kate Henshaw claims cleaner stabbed “Victims were rushed to the University of Ilorin Teaching Hospital by men of Oja Oba Police station after responding to the distress call, the victims were confirmed dead immediately they arrived at University of Ilorin Teaching Hospital (UITH) by the doctors on duty.” He revealed the suspected leader of the gang boys, also seriously injured, had been arrested He added: “The immediate/remote cause(s) of the fatal attack is yet to be unraveled. “However, the Commissioner of Police, Kwara State Police Command, Tuesday Assayomo has ordered a discreet investigation into the matter, by deploying strategies that would lead to the arrest of the fleeing attackers.” The command “assured the people of the area in particular and Kwara state in general of their safety and security at all times.”